 is fundamentally important for knowing what an 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

algebra
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is.
 I mean,
 duh,
 but that's what it is.
 I also didn't really know what an operator was.
 I mean,
 of course,
 linear,
 and of course,
 infinite–dimensional,
 but I was lacking in any formal grounding in operator theory.
 Both of these deficits have been cured.
 Many decades far too late,
 bu it is what it is.
\end_layout

